## Drift vs. extracted reality (the C4 boundary)
This is where authored intent hands off to graphify. graphify extracts the **real** module graph (the L4 "code" level) — actual imports, call edges, god-modules, community structure. Compare it to the components above: a module that has grown into a god-node, a dependency that shouldn't exist, a component that's pure intent with no code yet — each is **drift**. At `fleet`, the federated graph spans repos; reconcile drift as first-class work, don't let intent and reality silently diverge.
